[HR][/HR]

[SIZE=5][B][COLOR=#2e7d32]Features[/COLOR][/B][/SIZE]

[LIST]
[*][B]Biome-matched species[/B] - savanna acacias, dark-forest canopies, glacier pines, cherry groves, spiral-crown forests, and rainbow groves, mapped to the biomes they suit
[*][B]Procedural engine[/B] - trees are built in Java from per-species parameters: height, trunk shape, lean angle, and canopy layers
[*][B]Jigsaw worldgen[/B] - the plugin writes a vanilla worldgen datapack on first load and lets Minecraft's structure system place the trees
[*][B]Plantable saplings[/B] - [ICODE]/leaftree give[/ICODE] hands out NBT-tagged saplings that grow into a random variant when planted in a valid biome
[*][B]Reload command[/B] - [ICODE]/leaftree reload[/ICODE] rebakes all variants and regenerates the datapack
[*][B]Server-friendly placement[/B] - large trees are placed across multiple ticks under a per-tick budget to keep the main thread responsive
[*][B]Multi-platform[/B] - one jar runs on Paper, Folia, Fabric, and NeoForge with the same features (worldgen, saplings, and the [ICODE]/leaftree[/ICODE] command) everywhere
[/LIST]

[HR][/HR]

